## Early game

**Apollodorus** on Mercury (Survival) is one of the best Ferrite spots at any
gear level — the wiki calls it "probably one of the best ways to farm
Ferrite," citing over 4,000 per 10-minute rotation. Ferrite is a common enemy
drop, so it pours off the Grineer you kill; a Nekros loot squad and a Resource
Drop Booster push the numbers even higher, and popping the containers you pass
is a nice bonus on top. **M Prime** (Extermination), also on Mercury, is a
quick secondary stop when you just need a fast top-up.

## Mid & late game

Once Steel Path is unlocked, **Tikal** on Earth (Dark Sector Excavation) is a
strong endgame spot: a long Excavation keeps dense enemies spawning against the
excavators, and Ferrite drops from every one of them. Because it's an enemy
drop, the Steel Path resource-drop passive, a Resource Drop Booster and a loot
frame (Nekros/Khora) all stack — pair that with long run times and a squad
that keeps the kill count high for the biggest hauls.

